==Non-Ashkenazi disorders==
In contrast to the Ashkenazi population, [[Sephardic Jews|Sephardic]] and [[Oriental Jews]] are much more divergent groups, with ancestors from Spain, Portugal, Morocco, Tunisia, Algeria, Italy, Libya, the Balkans, Iran, Iraq, India and Yemen, with specific genetic disorders that are found in each regional group, or even in specific sub-populations in these regions.<ref name=Rosner>{{cite journal |author=Rosner G, Rosner S, Orr-Urtreger A |title=Genetic testing in Israel: an overview |journal=Annu Rev Genomics Hum Genet |volume=10 |issue= |pages=175–92 |year=2009 |pmid=19453249 |doi=10.1146/annurev.genom.030308.111406}}</ref>

